---
import ArticleLayout from "../../components/ArticleLayout.astro";

const title = "Entanglement: The Cosmic Link — Science";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<ArticleLayout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header>
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Atlas</a>
        <span class="chip">PHYSICS</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Entanglement: The Cosmic Link</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Entangled systems share one joint state, creating correlations that classical intuition cannot reproduce.</p>
      <p class="subtitle">{updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key ideas</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card"><h3>Correlation, not messaging</h3><p>Entanglement does not send usable information faster than light.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>One description for two systems</h3><p>You cannot fully describe each particle independently; the pair is the real object.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Verified in labs</h3><p>Bell-test experiments repeatedly rule out simple local hidden-variable models.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Mental model</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <ul>
        <li>Create an entangled pair from one interaction.</li>
        <li>Separate particles and choose measurement bases.</li>
        <li>Compare results later and observe correlations beyond classical limits.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Does entanglement break relativity?</summary><p>No. Relativity forbids faster-than-light signaling, and entanglement does not enable that.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Can entanglement survive in the real world?</summary><p>Yes, for limited times and distances; engineers fight noise to preserve coherence.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Where is it useful?</summary><p>Quantum cryptography, precision metrology, and quantum network research.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav">
      <a class="btn" href="/science">← Science index</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future">Explore Future →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>

</ArticleLayout>
